1. Initialize geth:
geth --datadir ./chaindata init genesis.json

2. Create new accounts:
./createAccounts.sh

3. Get list of accounts and update genesis.json to pre-allocate 100 ether
geth account list --datadir ./chaindata > accountlist.txt
python3 accounts.py

3a. Copy allocitem.txt to genesis.json

4. Remove ./chaindata/geth and re-initialize geth
rm -rf ./chaindata/geth
geth --datadir ./chaindata init genesis.json

4. Start the chain

geth --port 3000 --networkid 58343 --nodiscover --datadir=./chaindata --maxpeers=0 --rpc --rpcport 8543 --rpcaddr 127.0.0.1 --rpccorsdomain "*" --rpcapi "eth,net,web3,personal,miner" --allow-insecure-unlock --unlock "0" --password "123"

5. Start the miner

geth attach http://127.0.0.1:8543
miner.start() // sends all ether to accounts[0]